
command : chmod

Task	chmod Command Example
Change File Permissions (Symbolic Notation)	chmod permissions filename
Change File Permissions (Octal Notation)	chmod 644 filename
Change Directory Permissions (Symbolic Notation)	chmod permissions directoryname
Change Directory Permissions (Octal Notation)	chmod 755 directoryname
Recursively Change Permissions (Symbolic Notation)	chmod -R permissions directoryname
Recursively Change Permissions (Octal Notation)	chmod -R 755 directoryname


command: usermod

Certainly! Here's the information organized into a table:

Task	usermod Command Example
Change User's Username	sudo usermod -l newusername oldusername
Change User's Home Directory	sudo usermod -d /new/home/directory username
Change User's Shell	sudo usermod -s /bin/bash username
Change User's Primary Group	sudo usermod -g newprimarygroup username
Add User to Supplementary Groups	sudo usermod -aG group1,group2 username
Lock User Account	sudo usermod -L username
Unlock User Account	sudo usermod -U username
Set User Account Expiry Date	sudo usermod -e 2023-12-31 username
Force Password Change	sudo usermod -e 1970-01-01 username
Change User's User ID (UID)	(Not recommended; use with caution)
Change User's Group ID (GID)	(Not recommended; use with caution)
Modify User Comments or Information	sudo usermod -c "New Comment" username
Change Password Aging and Expiry Policies	Various options to manage password aging and expiry
Other Account Modifications	man usermod for a complete list of options
